org.csdgn.amf3

Class AmfByteArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.csdgn.amf3.AmfValue
      • org.csdgn.amf3.AmfByteArray

  • public class AmfByteArray
extends AmfValue
    This class handles byte buffer objects associated in the AMF. Internally makes use of an ArrayDeque. This class functions as a basic byte stack.
    Author:
    Robert Maupin

      • pop

        public byte[] pop(int count)

        Removes and returns the last count bytes in this array and decrements the byte array by this amount.

        This method is unlike multiple calls to pop() as it will get the values in the order they are in the byte array, where as multiple calls to pop() will return them in reverse order.

        Throws a IndexOutOfBoundsException if the count is larger than the size of this byte array.

        Parameters:
        count - Number of bytes to remove.
        Returns:
        The bytes popped from the array.

      • popTo

        public void popTo(byte[] b,
                  int offset,
                  int length)

        Removes the last length bytes in this arrayand stores them in b at offset and decrements the byte array by this amount.

        This method is unlike multiple calls to pop() as it will get the values in the order they are in the byte array, where as multiple calls to pop() will return them in reverse order.

        Throws a IndexOutOfBoundsException if the length is larger than the size of this byte array.

        Parameters:
        b - The byte array to write to.
        offset - The offset in the array to start writing at.
        length - The number of bytes to pop.

      • pushFrom

        public void pushFrom(byte[] b,
                     int offset,
                     int length)

        Appends length bytes from b starting at offset to the end of this byte array.

        Throws a IndexOutOfBoundsException if the offset plus the length is larger than the size of b.

        Parameters:
        b - The array containing the bytes to append.
        offset - The starting offset in b to start reading from.
        length - The number of bytes from b to append.
